description: Creates a model import job to import model that you have customized in other environments, such as Amazon SageMaker. For more information, see Import a customized model.

parameters.name: jobName
parameters.description: The name of the import job.

parameters.name: importedModelName
parameters.description: The name of the imported model.

parameters.name: roleArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the model import job.

parameters.name: modelDataSource
parameters.description: The data source for the imported model. s3DataSource (dict) --- The Amazon S3 data source of the imported model. The URI of the Amazon S3 data source.

nested_params.name: s3DataSource
nested_params.description: The Amazon S3 data source of the imported model.

nested_params.name: s3Uri
nested_params.description: The URI of the Amazon S3 data source.

parameters.name: jobTags
parameters.description: Tags to attach to this import job. (dict) --- Definition of the key/value pair for a tag. Key for the tag. Value for the tag.

parameters.name: importedModelTags
parameters.description: Tags to attach to the imported model. (dict) --- Definition of the key/value pair for a tag. Key for the tag. Value for the tag.

parameters.name: vpcConfig
parameters.description: VPC configuration parameters for the private Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) that contains the resources you are using for the import job. An array of IDs for each subnet in the VPC to use. (string) --- An array of IDs for each security group in the VPC to use. (string) ---

nested_params.name: subnetIds
nested_params.description: An array of IDs for each subnet in the VPC to use.

nested_params.name: securityGroupIds
nested_params.description: An array of IDs for each security group in the VPC to use.

nested_items.name: jobArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the model import job.
